    "name": "Material property and geometry sensitivity analysis for non-cannulated construct FEA",
    "description": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis varied Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (±10%), yield strength (±8%), screw outer diameter (±0.1 mm), and block spacing (±2 mm). Construct stiffness QoI showed greatest sensitivity to elastic modulus (normalized sensitivity index 0.82), while yield force was most sensitive to yield strength (index 0.91). All sensitivities were bounded within the uncertainty budget, confirming that the dominant uncertainty sources are adequately characterized in the uval computation."
